<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="62" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1369,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1369,1393]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Both males and females of 
<emphasis box="[617,897,1370,1393]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Melichyopharis 
<taxonomicName box="[792,897,1370,1393]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Melychiopharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bibendum">bibendum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
differ from 
<taxonomicName box="[1030,1130,1370,1393]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Melychiopharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinips">
<emphasis box="[1030,1130,1370,1393]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">M. cinips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Santos" box="[1188,1385,1369,1393]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" refString="Santos, A. J., Brescovit, A. D. &amp; Levi, H. W. (2005) Melychiopharis: an atypical orb-weaving spider from South America (Araneae: Araneidae). Zootaxa, 1016, 57 - 64." type="journal article" year="2005">
Santos 
<emphasis box="[1266,1321,1370,1393]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1328,1385,1369,1392]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: figs 
<number box="[151,205,1403,1426]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="8.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="6.0">6–10</number>
) in the stronger granulation of carapace (
<figureCitation box="[673,782,1403,1426]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,181,1230]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 1, Male habitus, dorsal view; 2, female habitus, dorsal view; 3, male pedipalp, prolateral view; 4, ditto, retrolateral view; 5, female abdomen, ventral view; 7, ditto, antero-ventral view (arrow points to anterior tubercles). Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277031/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Figs. 1, 2</figureCitation>
) and in the remarkable tubercles at the anterior margin of abdomen, around the pedicel (
<figureCitation box="[473,539,1437,1460]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,181,1230]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 1, Male habitus, dorsal view; 2, female habitus, dorsal view; 3, male pedipalp, prolateral view; 4, ditto, retrolateral view; 5, female abdomen, ventral view; 7, ditto, antero-ventral view (arrow points to anterior tubercles). Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277031/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[523,539,1437,1460]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Males also differ in the longer embolus with a small rounded basis (
<figureCitation box="[1282,1357,1437,1460]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,181,1230]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 1, Male habitus, dorsal view; 2, female habitus, dorsal view; 3, male pedipalp, prolateral view; 4, ditto, retrolateral view; 5, female abdomen, ventral view; 7, ditto, antero-ventral view (arrow points to anterior tubercles). Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277031/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1369,1383,1437,1460]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1311,1334]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,592,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,583,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 7, Male pedipalp, prolateral view; 8, ditto, retrolateral view; 9, female epigynum, ventral view; 10, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; M, median plate of epigynum; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium; SP, spermathecae. Scale bars: 4.7 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277032/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">7</figureCitation>
) and the larger paracymbium (
<figureCitation box="[421,486,1471,1494]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,181,1230]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 1, Male habitus, dorsal view; 2, female habitus, dorsal view; 3, male pedipalp, prolateral view; 4, ditto, retrolateral view; 5, female abdomen, ventral view; 7, ditto, antero-ventral view (arrow points to anterior tubercles). Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277031/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[498,513,1471,1494]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1311,1334]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,592,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,583,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 7, Male pedipalp, prolateral view; 8, ditto, retrolateral view; 9, female epigynum, ventral view; 10, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; M, median plate of epigynum; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium; SP, spermathecae. Scale bars: 4.7 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277032/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">8</figureCitation>
). Females can be distinguished by the median plate of epigynum subtriangular, with a narrow anterior septum (
<figureCitation box="[414,489,1505,1528]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,181,1230]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 1, Male habitus, dorsal view; 2, female habitus, dorsal view; 3, male pedipalp, prolateral view; 4, ditto, retrolateral view; 5, female abdomen, ventral view; 7, ditto, antero-ventral view (arrow points to anterior tubercles). Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277031/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[501,515,1505,1528]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1311,1334]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,592,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,583,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 7, Male pedipalp, prolateral view; 8, ditto, retrolateral view; 9, female epigynum, ventral view; 10, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; M, median plate of epigynum; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium; SP, spermathecae. Scale bars: 4.7 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277032/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">9</figureCitation>
) and the copulatory ducts wider and not encapsulated (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1183,1505,1528]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1311,1334]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,592,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,583,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 7, Male pedipalp, prolateral view; 8, ditto, retrolateral view; 9, female epigynum, ventral view; 10, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; M, median plate of epigynum; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium; SP, spermathecae. Scale bars: 4.7 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277032/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[1153,1183,1505,1528]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1369,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,331,1538,1562]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Description</emphasis>
. Male. Carapace longer than wide, widest at the middle. Carapace, sternum and legs red-brown. Lateral and part of dorsum of opisthosoma yellow, with a large central, brown spot and two posterior marginal black patches (
<figureCitation box="[159,223,1606,1629]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,181,1230]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 1, Male habitus, dorsal view; 2, female habitus, dorsal view; 3, male pedipalp, prolateral view; 4, ditto, retrolateral view; 5, female abdomen, ventral view; 7, ditto, antero-ventral view (arrow points to anterior tubercles). Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277031/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[210,223,1606,1629]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Venter reddish anteriorly and orange posteriorly. Eyes subequal in size. Anterior median eyes separated by its diameters, almost one diameter from posterior medians. Lateral eyes approximately half a diameter from the anterior medians. Median ocular quadrangle almost square. Clypeus 
<number box="[803,836,1674,1697]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.5">1.5</number>
anterior median eyes diameter high. Opisthosoma 
<number box="[1389,1436,1674,1697]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.1">1.10</number>
long, 1.0 wide, covered with a single, dish-shaped dorsal scutum, with a lateral flange (
<figureCitation box="[1099,1163,1708,1731]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,181,1230]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 1, Male habitus, dorsal view; 2, female habitus, dorsal view; 3, male pedipalp, prolateral view; 4, ditto, retrolateral view; 5, female abdomen, ventral view; 7, ditto, antero-ventral view (arrow points to anterior tubercles). Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277031/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[1150,1163,1708,1731]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Venter with an anterior and a posterior sclerotized area to the epigastric groove. Anterior sclerotized area with a marked posterior sulcus. Colulus small, without setae. Total length 
<number box="[523,559,1776,1799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.1">2.1</number>
. Carapace 1.0 long, 
<number box="[785,818,1776,1799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="0.6">0.6</number>
wide. Femur I 
<number box="[991,1027,1776,1799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.2">2.2</number>
, patella and tibia 
<number box="[1224,1259,1776,1799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.8">1.8</number>
, metatarsus 
<number box="[1396,1431,1776,1799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.2">1.2</number>
, tarsus 
<number box="[219,256,1810,1833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="0.7">0.7</number>
. Patella and tibia II 
<number box="[468,503,1810,1833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.7">1.7</number>
, III 
<number box="[548,583,1810,1833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.3">1.3</number>
, IV 
<number box="[629,665,1810,1833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.8">1.8</number>
. Legs without femoral spines. Macrosetae absent on male palpal patella. Tegulum elongated mesally, with a rounded, sclerotized hump. Median apophysis distally bent (
<figureCitation box="[1167,1242,1843,1866]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,181,1230]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 1, Male habitus, dorsal view; 2, female habitus, dorsal view; 3, male pedipalp, prolateral view; 4, ditto, retrolateral view; 5, female abdomen, ventral view; 7, ditto, antero-ventral view (arrow points to anterior tubercles). Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277031/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1253,1269,1843,1866]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1311,1334]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,592,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,583,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 7, Male pedipalp, prolateral view; 8, ditto, retrolateral view; 9, female epigynum, ventral view; 10, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; M, median plate of epigynum; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium; SP, spermathecae. Scale bars: 4.7 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277032/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">7</figureCitation>
). Paracymbium curved, convex, and rectangular in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[664,739,1877,1900]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,181,1230]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 1, Male habitus, dorsal view; 2, female habitus, dorsal view; 3, male pedipalp, prolateral view; 4, ditto, retrolateral view; 5, female abdomen, ventral view; 7, ditto, antero-ventral view (arrow points to anterior tubercles). Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277031/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[751,766,1877,1900]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1311,1334]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,592,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,583,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 7, Male pedipalp, prolateral view; 8, ditto, retrolateral view; 9, female epigynum, ventral view; 10, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; M, median plate of epigynum; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium; SP, spermathecae. Scale bars: 4.7 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277032/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1369,2036]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,152,548]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Female. Body shape and coloration as in male (
<figureCitation box="[722,858,1911,1934]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,181,1230]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 1, Male habitus, dorsal view; 2, female habitus, dorsal view; 3, male pedipalp, prolateral view; 4, ditto, retrolateral view; 5, female abdomen, ventral view; 7, ditto, antero-ventral view (arrow points to anterior tubercles). Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277031/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Figs. 2, 5, 
<number box="[842,858,1911,1934]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Relative eye interdistances as in male. Clypeus 
<number box="[1403,1436,1911,1934]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.5">2.5</number>
anterior median eyes diameter high. Total length 
<number box="[695,731,1945,1968]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="2.2">2.2</number>
, carapace 
<number box="[846,879,1945,1968]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="0.9">0.9</number>
long, 
<number box="[953,987,1945,1968]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="0.6">0.6</number>
wide. Femur I 
<number box="[1161,1197,1945,1968]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="0.8">0.8</number>
, patella and tibia 2.0, metatarsus 
<number box="[274,310,1979,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.4">1.4</number>
, tarsus 
<number box="[394,431,1979,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="0.7">0.7</number>
. Patella and tibia II 
<number box="[655,691,1979,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.9">1.9</number>
, III 
<number box="[740,776,1979,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.4">1.4</number>
, IV 
<number box="[826,862,1979,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.7">1.7</number>
. Legs without femoral spines. Macrosetae absent on female palpal patella. Opisthosoma 
<number box="[542,575,2013,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.2">1.2</number>
long, 
<number box="[647,681,2013,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="1.1">1.1</number>
wide, similar to the male, except by the shorter posterior sclerotized area (
<figureCitation box="[211,277,152,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,187,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,181,1230]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 1, Male habitus, dorsal view; 2, female habitus, dorsal view; 3, male pedipalp, prolateral view; 4, ditto, retrolateral view; 5, female abdomen, ventral view; 7, ditto, antero-ventral view (arrow points to anterior tubercles). Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277031/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[262,277,152,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Copulatory openings located on the side of the median plate of epigynum. Copulatory ducts long, twisted and enlarged on the base of spermathecae. Spermathecae rounded and close together. Fertilization ducts long, basal to the spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[310,390,219,242]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1311,1334]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,592,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,583,1290]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Melychiopharis bibendum n. sp. 7, Male pedipalp, prolateral view; 8, ditto, retrolateral view; 9, female epigynum, ventral view; 10, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; M, median plate of epigynum; MA, median apophysis; PC, paracymbium; SP, spermathecae. Scale bars: 4.7 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277032/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[360,390,219,242]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="63" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,548]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,253,277]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Remarks.</emphasis>
The long and granulated carapace of the 
<typeStatus box="[748,794,253,276]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">type</typeStatus>
specimens, together with the genitalic characters mentioned in the genus diagnosis supports the placement of this species in 
<taxonomicName box="[934,1101,287,310]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Melychiopharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[934,1101,287,310]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Melychiopharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[1124,1291,287,310]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Melychiopharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1124,1291,287,310]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Melychiopharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably monophyletic, supported by at least the modified carapace and the filiform median apophysis (see additional comments in 
<bibRefCitation author="Santos" box="[178,373,355,378]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" refString="Santos, A. J., Brescovit, A. D. &amp; Levi, H. W. (2005) Melychiopharis: an atypical orb-weaving spider from South America (Araneae: Araneidae). Zootaxa, 1016, 57 - 64." type="journal article" year="2005">
Santos et al. 
<number box="[315,373,355,378]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,548]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,374,388,412]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Natural history</emphasis>
. The specimens were collected by nocturnal visual search on 
<collectingCountry box="[1052,1107,388,411]" name="Malta" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Mata</collectingCountry>
Atlântica area of the 
<collectingCountry box="[1346,1401,388,411]" name="Malta" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Mata</collectingCountry>
do Pacangê, in the south of Bahia, but unfortunately the web was not observed by the collectors. The specimens were found at low abundance (only two individuals) in a study where 
<number box="[770,830,456,479]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="2406.0">2,406</number>
spider specimens were collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1181,490,514]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,548]" box="[199,1181,490,514]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,490,514]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Distribution</emphasis>
. Know only from the 
<typeStatus box="[575,621,490,513]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">type</typeStatus>
locality in the state of Bahia, northeastern of 
<collectingCountry box="[1108,1177,490,513]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
